The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, August 01, 2004 				 L amp;T net up 26% 
																								Mumbai, July 31 (PTI): Larsen amp; Toubro Ltd (L amp;T) has posted a 26.12 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 80.13 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, 2004 against Rs 63.53 crore in the year-ago period even as the engineering major estimated a 25 per cent growth in its sales in the current fiscal. The net sales for the reporting quarter rose to Rs 2,639.37 crore against Rs 1,564.93 crore in April-June 2004, the company said in a release here today.Marginal rise in Bajaj Auto bottomline																								Bajaj Auto Ltd today reported a marginal rise in its net profit for the first quarter ended June 30, 2004, at Rs 164.5 crore compared with Rs 161.1 crore in the same quarter last fiscal. Total income rose to Rs 1,332.6 crore from Rs 1,183.9 crore recorded in April-June 2003-04, the company said in a release. 																								About 700 workmen at the companys Akurdi plant have opted for voluntary retirement under the scheme announced on July 1, 2004, it said, adding, a liability of Rs 48.2 crore on account of the VRS would be charged over the next three quarters of the current fiscal. 																								Exports for the June quarter were up 33 per cent at Rs 171.4 crore against Rs 128.4 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal. 
